<item>
            <title>[SLING-3464] The DynamicClassLoaderManager doesn&apos;t reload classes when a bundle transitions from ACTIVE to RESOLVED</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SLING-3464</link>
                <project id="12310710" key="SLING">Sling</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The bundle activator from org.apache.sling.commons.classloader also acts as a SynchronousBundleListener, taking care to clean the DynamicClassLoaderManager (DCLM) when a bundle changes its state.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the DCLM doesn&apos;t get cleaned when a bundle transitions from ACTIVE to RESOLVED, which is inconsistent: for example no services will be resolved from that bundle, however classes already loaded through DCLM will get solved.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12702398">SLING-3464</key>
            <summary>The DynamicClassLoaderManager doesn&apos;t reload classes when a bundle transitions from ACTIVE to RESOLVED</summary>
